1
00:00:03,696 --> 00:00:07,321
And Rūpa Gosvāmī mentions this
in the Bhakti-rasāmṛta-sindhu,

2
00:00:07,321 --> 00:00:09,235
“You have to be
Kṛṣṇa conscious,

3
00:00:09,235 --> 00:00:12,251
you can’t be Kṛṣṇa conscious
for someone else,

4
00:00:12,251 --> 00:00:14,456
and someone else 
can’t be designated

5
00:00:14,456 --> 00:00:16,576
to be Kṛṣṇa conscious 
for you.”

6
00:00:16,626 --> 00:00:21,350
[Show by Example | Offer Yourself]

7
00:00:21,480 --> 00:00:25,992
Bhaktivedānta Manor in England—
they have this big temple

8
00:00:25,992 --> 00:00:29,392
that George Harrison
donated to the devotees,

9
00:00:29,392 --> 00:00:32,515
and Prabhupād then installed
the Deities there.

10
00:00:32,515 --> 00:00:36,652
So like, they have 50,000
people go to the temple sometimes.

11
00:00:36,652 --> 00:00:38,298
So, in a little town, 
first everyone thought,

12
00:00:38,298 --> 00:00:41,298
they’re not going to …

13
00:00:41,298 --> 00:00:43,832
They’re going to be 
very unhappy with the devotees.

14
00:00:43,832 --> 00:00:50,342
Like, the local pub owner—
he was very happy.

15
00:00:50,342 --> 00:00:52,142
And we’re going, 
“Why would the pub owner …?”

16
00:00:52,142 --> 00:00:54,919
We say,
“No elicit sex, no intoxication.”

17
00:00:54,919 --> 00:00:57,076
Why would the pub owner
be happy?

18
00:00:57,076 --> 00:00:59,042
Because what he found is
these Indian men

19
00:00:59,042 --> 00:01:01,476
were dropping their wives off 
at the temple,

20
00:01:01,476 --> 00:01:03,010
and then they all 
would go to the pub,

21
00:01:03,010 --> 00:01:06,243
and sit there, and drink Guinness,
or whatever they drink.

22
00:01:06,243 --> 00:01:08,373
[Laughing]

23
00:01:11,196 --> 00:01:15,729
So the pub owner is like,
“Hare Kṛṣṇa prabhu.”

24
00:01:15,729 --> 00:01:19,370
[Laughing]

25
00:01:19,370 --> 00:01:20,346
But my point is …
you might say:

26
00:01:20,346 --> 00:01:25,515
“Why I am mentioning this 
other than for comedic effect?”
 

27
00:01:25,515 --> 00:01:27,555
Is that,
their idea was like,

28
00:01:27,555 --> 00:01:30,955
“Oh, my wife,
she is the religious one.”

29
00:01:30,955 --> 00:01:33,814
So they think, “I am at the pub
drinking Guinness,

30
00:01:33,814 --> 00:01:37,145
and my wife’s bowing down
before the Deity, and doing some seva,

31
00:01:37,145 --> 00:01:40,908
I’m doing pretty good.”
[Laughing]

32
00:01:40,908 --> 00:01:45,638
Or my child will be
Kṛṣṇa conscious,

33
00:01:45,658 --> 00:01:48,468
or the husband—the wife,
the wife—the husband,

34
00:01:48,468 --> 00:01:51,805
the parents—the children,
the children—the parents, etc.

35
00:01:51,805 --> 00:01:53,572
So, there is 
a nice śloka,
 

36
00:01:53,572 --> 00:01:54,745
which I haven’t committed 
to memory,

37
00:01:54,745 --> 00:01:58,843
but Guru Mahārāj mentions
from Bhakti-rasāmṛta-sindhu,

38
00:01:58,843 --> 00:02:01,360
where Rūpa Gosvāmī mentions
all of these …

39
00:02:01,360 --> 00:02:05,782
It’s not, you can just like 
buy it, either.

40
00:02:05,782 --> 00:02:09,508
You can’t have a surrogate,
 

41
00:02:09,508 --> 00:02:13,332
where someone is going to be 
accumulating Kṛṣṇa consciousness for you,

42
00:02:13,332 --> 00:02:17,442
and then transfer it to you.

43
00:02:17,442 --> 00:02:24,272
Neither can you purchase it,
like they used to have long ago.

44
00:02:27,427 --> 00:02:31,010
It’s good to engage your wealth,
your money, your wife, your family …

45
00:02:31,010 --> 00:02:33,930
That’s good, 
but still you, 
 

46
00:02:33,930 --> 00:02:38,650
it’s about ātma-samarpaṇam—
offering yourself.

47
00:02:38,650 --> 00:02:42,729
So, if you say, if we rephrase
the original question and say,

48
00:02:42,729 --> 00:02:47,897
“How can I get someone to engage
in ātma-samarpaṇam—self-giving?”

49
00:02:47,897 --> 00:02:55,230
Well, usually the best way is
to show by example,

50
00:02:55,230 --> 00:02:58,060
to offer yourself 
in service,

51
00:02:58,060 --> 00:03:03,260
and be the personification
of a desirable outcome.

52
00:03:03,260 --> 00:03:06,328
And they’ll see,
“Oh, I see Kṛṣṇa consciousness

53
00:03:06,328 --> 00:03:08,916
is having a good effect 
upon this person”.

54
00:03:08,916 --> 00:03:13,356
It may awaken 
some interest in them.

55
00:03:16,427 --> 00:03:25,947
But to try and, like cajole,
or what’s another word,

56
00:03:29,595 --> 00:03:33,275
to make someone 
feel guilt, or whatever,

57
00:03:33,275 --> 00:03:38,950
and try and intimidate them

58
00:03:38,950 --> 00:03:43,705
into taking up the culture 
of Kṛṣṇa consciousness,

59
00:03:43,705 --> 00:03:46,945
that’s not, as I said 
in Gurudev’s words:

60
00:03:46,945 --> 00:03:48,915
“Not to force.”

